-- this module contains the functions
-- rand() rand implements pseudo-random number generators suitable for tasks such as simulation, but it should not be used for security-sensitive work.
-- randv2() rand implements pseudo-random number generators suitable for tasks such as simulation, but it should not be used for security-sensitive work.
-- cmplx() cmplx provides basic constants and mathematical functions for complex numbers.
-- bits() bits implements bit counting and manipulation functions for the predeclared unsigned integer types.
-- big() big implements arbitrary-precision arithmetic (big numbers).